<Base title="DiveCraft — Case Study" description="Procedural islands, blocky wave simulation, and chunked terrain meshing.">
  <h1>DiveCraft — Blocky Waves & Procedural Islands</h1>
  <p class="muted">Role: Solo • Tech: Unity 2022 LTS, C# • Time: 2025</p>
  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Goal</h2>
    <p>Create a performant vertical slice: island proc-gen, stylised block waves, and chunk meshing at 60 FPS on mid-range hardware.</p>
    <h2>Highlights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Chunked terrain meshing (16×16) with greedy mesh combine.</li>
      <li>Block-wave system (step-style) driven by phase buckets.</li>
      <li>Editor tools for captures and profiling.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Deep-dive</h2>
    <div class="code"><pre><code>// Wave update pseudocode
for each chunk in loadedChunks:
  phase = (globalTick + chunk.hash) % NUM_PHASES
  for cell in chunk.surfaceCells[phase]:
    cell.height = base + stepHeights[phase]
</code></pre></div>
